:: AreaFocusedSuccess
<<set $step = 0>><<ShowInfo>><<set $day += 60>><<GenerateTimeSkipWorries 60>>

<h3>Frugality Pays Off</h3>
<div class="consequence-text">
	<p>Four months of disciplined, area-focused work. Four months of saying no to jobs outside your zone, but saying yes to every opportunity within it.</p>
	<p>It's been tight. Some weeks you wondered if you'd made a mistake. You watched other workers take jobs all over the city, seemingly making more money. You heard about opportunities you had to turn down.</p>
	<p>But you stuck to your strategy. Every rideshare dollar saved went into a jar at home. Every week, you and your wife counted it together: $50, $100, $200, $400, $800.</p>
	<p>And something unexpected happened: by becoming the reliable worker in your specific area, you became known. The job coordinators in that neighborhood started calling you first. "I know you're always around here," one says. "I can count on you to show up."</p>
	<p>Local homeowners started asking for you by name. Small business owners recommended you to each other. You lost the city-wide opportunities, but you gained a neighborhood reputation.</p>
	<p>The income was steady. Not spectacular, but consistent. And with your disciplined approach to transportation costs, you've been saving.</p>
	<p>One evening, you count the savings and realize you have enough for a car - but cars are expensive. A decent used vehicle costs around $1,600.</p>
</div>
<hr>

